,'<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ergo Flight UltraLight Wheelchair Features:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>14.5 lb. Frame / 19.8 lb. (w/o footrest)</p>\r\n<p>Revolutionizing and pushing T6 Grade Aluminum Geometry and Technology to its best to compete with Titanium saving YOU more than 71% in price!</p>\r\n<p>*For quick ship checkout, our standard base models will be shipped in 18&Prime; seat width.&nbsp; You may also customize it on the drop-down menu below.</p>\r\n<p>The ERGO FLIGHT Ultralight Wheelchair is a fantastic design. It&rsquo;s pricey but well worth it, and not to be missed! Recommended for people with long-term mobility issues in mind. If you have a short-term need for a wheelchair, some other model will probably be a better overall &ldquo;fit&rdquo; despite this one&rsquo;s quality. Do you have a long-term mobility issue?&nbsp; If you do, then it changes what you&rsquo;re looking for in a wheelchair.&nbsp; After all, if your needs are short-term, most any decent chair will work. However,&nbsp; if you know you&rsquo;re going to need a mobility aid for months and years to come, then you start getting much more particular and asking hard questions about what you want in a wheelchair.</p>\r\n<p>We understand, which is why if the above describes you, we think you&rsquo;re going to love our in-depth review of the ERGO FLIGHT Ergonomic wheelchair.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Ergonomic&rdquo; is more than just a buzzword.&nbsp; An ergonomically designed chair is just more comfortable to sit in, and easier to use because everything is exactly where you&rsquo;d expect to find it.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s intuitive, and if your needs are long-term, that&rsquo;s pure gold.</p>\r\n<p>There are a lot of wheelchairs on the market.&nbsp; An almost overwhelming number of choices that can lead to analysis paralysis.&nbsp; To help you cut through the clutter, we are here to help so you can make an informed purchasing decision.</p>\r\n<p>By any measure, the ERGO FLIGHT wheelchair is an exceptional model.&nbsp; In fact, it won top honors on our roundup review of the best wheelchairs being sold today.&nbsp; In the sections that follow, we&rsquo;ll walk you through everything this fantastic chair can do, and let you know about its (very few) limitations so you can decide for yourself if it&rsquo;s the &ldquo;right&rdquo; model for you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT FEATURES</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Weighs only 19.8 lbs (w/out footrest) ; 14.5 lbs (w/out QR wheels &amp; footrest)</li>\r\n<li>Lightest T6 Alu Manual Propel wheelchair on the market</li>\r\n<li>Globally Patented S-Style Ergonomic Seat Frame</li>\r\n<li>6061 T-6 Aircraft-grade Aluminum</li>\r\n<li>Built-in Aegis Anti-bacterial Padded Upholstery</li>\r\n<li>Fixed Armrest with Desk Length Ergonomic Padded Arm Pads</li>\r\n<li>Storage Pocket Behind Backrest</li>\r\n<li>Folding Backrest and Folding Seat</li>\r\n<li>Swing In/Away Removable footrest</li>\r\n<li>Companion Brakes Standard</li>\r\n<li>6&rdquo; x 1&rdquo; Polyurethane Front Casters</li>\r\n<li>20&rdquo; x 1 3/8&rdquo; Rear Polyurethane, High Tread, Flat Free Wheels</li>\r\n<li>16&rdquo; x 17&rdquo; or 18&rdquo; x 17&rdquo; Seat Width</li>\r\n<li>Weight Capacity of 220 lbs</li>\r\n<li>Frame Color: Pearl Silver</li>\r\n<li>WARRANTY</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table style=\"width: 345.663px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 141px;\">HCPCS Code</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 208.663px;\">K0004</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 141px;\">Seat Width</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 208.663px;\">16\", 18\"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 141px;\">Seat Depth</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 208.663px;\">17\"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 141px;\">Armrest Height</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 208.663px;\">8\"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 141px;\">Seat Height</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 208.663px;\">19\"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 141px;\">Back Height</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 208.