 YOU more than 71% in price!</p>\r\n<p>*For quick ship checkout, our standard base models will be shipped in 18&Prime; seat width.&nbsp; You may also customize it on the drop-down menu below.</p>\r\n<p>The ERGO FLIGHT Ultralight Wheelchair is a fantastic design. It&rsquo;s pricey but well worth it, and not to be missed! Recommended for people with long-term mobility issues in mind. If you have a short-term need for a wheelchair, some other model will probably be a better overall &ldquo;fit&rdquo; despite this one&rsquo;s quality. Do you have a long-term mobility issue?&nbsp; If you do, then it changes what you&rsquo;re looking for in a wheelchair.&nbsp; After all, if your needs are short-term, most any decent chair will work. However,&nbsp; if you know you&rsquo;re going to need a mobility aid for months and years to come, then you start getting much more particular and asking hard questions about what you want in a wheelchair.</p>\r\n<p>We understand, which is why if the above describes you, we think you&rsquo;re going to love our in-depth review of the ERGO FLIGHT Ergonomic wheelchair.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Ergonomic&rdquo; is more than just a buzzword.&nbsp; An ergonomically designed chair is just more comfortable to sit in, and easier to use because everything is exactly where you&rsquo;d expect to find it.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s intuitive, and if your needs are long-term, that&rsquo;s pure gold.</p>\r\n<p>There are a lot of wheelchairs on the market.&nbsp; An almost overwhelming number of choices that can lead to analysis paralysis.&nbsp; To help you cut through the clutter, we are here to help so you can make an informed purchasing decision.</p>\r\n<p>By any measure, the ERGO FLIGHT wheelchair is an exceptional model.&nbsp; In fact, it won top honors on our roundup review of the best wheelchairs being sold today.&nbsp; In the sections that follow, we&rsquo;ll walk you through everything this fantastic chair can do, and let you know about its (very few) limitations so you